						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar set up in front of the Vēṇugōpalasvāmi temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Plava, Kārttīka, śu. 15.</p>						

						<p>Two inscriptions engraved on a pillar, the first one mentions the services to the god Gōpalasvāmi by Śrī Giri, son of Sōmarāju Tiṁmarāju; the second inscription mentions some services to the god Gōpalasvāmi of Guḍipāṭi by Narasiṁha, son of Rāmanna on the given date.</p>						

						</summary>
